s.\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 4039, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A much more structural solution\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3955}, {\"ngram\": \"the pretty clean rainwater\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 4003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Doing that for all existing sewers and connections would be an awfully big and expensive job, and certainly much more than \\u00a31bn,\\\" said Buytaert.\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all existing sewers\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4074}, {\"ngram\": \"connections\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"an awfully big and expensive job\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4132}, {\"ngram\": \"Buytaert\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A good place to start is with new building developments, which now require separation of rain and sewage.\\\"\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4293, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A good place\", \"from\": 4187, \"to\": 4199}, {\"ngram\": \"new building developments\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4242}, {\"ngram\": \"separation\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4272}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4280}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4291}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Households could stop rainwater entering the sewage system through water butts, freeing up space for the system to deal with sewage, suggested Buytaert.\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4446, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Households\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4304}, {\"ngram\": \"rainwater\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4325}, {\"ngram\": \"the sewage system\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4352}, {\"ngram\": \"water butts\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4372}, {\"ngram\": \"space\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4390}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 4395, \"to\": 4405}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4425}, {\"ngram\": \"Buytaert\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Action on the water industry is also needed, said Watson: \\\"Here in the UK, the newly elected Labour government has promised to take on the broken water industry that has poisoned our rivers with human sewage.\", \"from\": 4448, \"to\": 4656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4498, \"end\": 4504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"score\": 0.9999443260445154, \"rank\": 5.169161408388718e-05, \"text\": \"Watson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\"}, {\"begin\": 4519, \"end\": 4521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999976225718522, \"rank\": 2.377430387073306e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4541, \"end\": 4547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.8944515695506109, \"rank\": 0.11799652025284063, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Action\", \"from\": 4448, \"to\": 4454}, {\"ngram\": \"the water industry\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4476}, {\"ngram\": \"the broken water industry\", \"from\": 4583, \"to\": 4608}, {\"ngram\": \"our rivers\", \"from\": 4627, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"human sewage\", \"from\": 4643, \"to\": 4655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it's not only the water companies that should be worried.\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4720, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the water companies\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We also need urgent action to reduce pollution from industrial-scale agriculture that has, for example, caused ecological collapse on the River Wye.\", \"from\": 4721, \"t